    <text id="F4052T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>This letter fragment, written in difficult handwriting, mentions the capture of
                    Pennyslvanian property on that expedition.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
             

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-06-25">June 25th 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Camp near Chambersburg Pa</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Darling Wife</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> this are anxious to hear from me and as I have a way to send
                    a letter by a <orig reg="wagon">waggon</orig> to winchester I hurry to write you
                    a few lines I am now where I never <unclear>was</unclear> in this state farther
                    north than I ever expected to be but it seem that from our course we are still
                    going farther we have had no difficulty got no fight Captured a quantity of
                    stores Horses Cattle and various other things I am well I would like to write
                    more but have not the time all of the boys are well I have two dresses and a
                    pair of shoes for you if I can find a way to send them I <unclear>will</unclear>
                    <unclear>close</unclear> for <unclear>Monday</unclear>
                    <pb n="2"/></p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed/>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
